		{ value: '~23,000', label: 'homicides in 2024 — much of it cartel violence; 300,000+ killed in a decade' },
		{ value: '~half', label: 'of the population lives below the poverty line' },
		{ value: '~400,000', label: 'orphaned children; an estimated 100,000 live on the streets' },
		{ value: '1 in 5', label: 'children experience a father’s migration by age 15 — the leading cause of father absence' },
		{ value: '1 in 11', label: 'children see their father leave for the United States' },
		{ value: '18% of GDP', label: 'the economic toll of violence in 2024' },
	]}
	painsBodyHtml={`<p>Cartel violence has taken a generation; poverty grips half the nation; and migration &mdash; often the only path to provide &mdash; has made the <strong>absent father</strong> the defining wound of countless Mexican homes. Children grow up with a father&rsquo;s photo on the wall and his voice on the phone, but his chair empty at the table.</p><p>These are not statistics to a Father. They are children He longs to gather. Mexico does not need more religion &mdash; it needs to know it is loved by a Father who never leaves.</p>`}
	painsSources={[
		{ label: 'Mexico homicide & violence 2024 (Vision of Humanity)', url: 'https://www.visionofhumanity.org/mexicos-organised-criminal-landscape-2025/' },
		{ label: 'Migration & father absence in Mexico (Demography)', url: 'https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s13524-012-0187-8' },
	]}
	faithsHeading="What “our Father” offers Mexico"
	faithsIntroHtml={`Mexico already believes. The Father&rsquo;s Heart Bible&trade; does not bring a new religion &mdash; it answers the longing underneath the faith Mexico already holds: to know God not at a distance, but as a Father who is near. For the first time in a fresh translation, Scripture reveals Him not as a remote figure, but as a <em>Father</em> who runs to meet His children.`}
	faithsBlocks={[
		{ heading: 'For the one who keeps the faith from afar', bodyHtml: `If God has felt distant &mdash; approached through ritual and intermediaries &mdash; the Father&rsquo;s Heart Bible&trade; reveals <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read/luke/15" style="color: var(--color-gold);" class="hover:underline">the Father who runs to the returning child</a>, near enough to embrace.` },
		{ heading: 'For the fatherless and the left-behind', bodyHtml: `To every child whose father crossed a border to provide, Scripture promises <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read/psalms/68" style="color: var(--color-gold);" class="hover:underline">&ldquo;a father to the fatherless&rdquo;</a> &mdash; a Father who never migrates away, who is always at the table.` },
		{ heading: 'For the grieving and the afraid', bodyHtml: `In a nation marked by violence and loss, the Father offers a love stronger than fear &mdash; comfort for the mourning and a refuge that cartels cannot touch.` },
